New Records: Cameroon scored four goals with contributions from Vincent Aboubakar, Martin Hongla, Bryan Mbeumo, and Christian Bassogog.
Kenya scored one goal through Michael Olunga.
Key Match Events: Vincent Aboubakar scored an early penalty.
Bryan Mbeumo and Christian Bassogog added to Cameroon's goals.
Final score of 4-1 in favor of Cameroon.
Post-Match Reflections: Harambee Stars coach Engin Firat faced his heaviest defeat since taking charge.
Kenya's performance was described as flat-footed and lacking in contention.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Patrick Matasi returned to the starting team.
Amos Nondi was substituted for Joseph Okumu.
